1. Functional Requirements
(What the system should do)
-->📞 Contacts Module (Linked List)
1.Add new contact (name & number)
2.Display all contacts
3.Store contacts dynamically
-->💬 Messages Module (Queue)
1.Send/store messages
2.View all messages in order (FIFO)
3.Delete oldest message
-->📱 Call History Module (Stack)
1.Store call history
2.Display recent calls (LIFO)
3.Delete last call
-->🎛️ Main System
1.Menu-driven interface
2.Perform operations based on user choice
3.Exit option

 2. Non-Functional Requirements
(How the system should behave)
1.Simple and easy-to-use interface
2.Fast execution
3.Efficient memory usage (dynamic allocation for contacts)
4.Organized code using functions and data structures

 3. Hardware Requirements
1.Computer / Laptop
2.Minimum 2GB RAM
3.Keyboard for input

 4. Software Requirements
1.C++ Compiler (GCC / Code::Blocks / Turbo C++)
2.Operating System (Windows / Linux / Mac)

 5. Input Requirements
1.Contact name and number
2.Message text
3.Call name
4.Menu choice (1–9)

 6. Output Requirements
1.Display contact list
2.Show messages
3.Show call history
4.Confirmation messages (Added / Deleted / Calling)
